adminCollectFees(address,uint256).details: can only be called by owner

params.amount: will be trasnfered to owner if contract balace is higher or equal to amount

params.amountOrTokenID: Either the amount of ERC20 tokens or the ERC721 token ID to withdraw.
params.handlerAddress: Address of handler to withdraw from.

params.amountOrTokenID: Either the amount of ERC20 tokens or the ERC721 token ID to approve.

params.amountToLA: to be converted to LA with bridge swap.
params.destinationChainID: ID of chain deposit will be bridged to.
params.resourceID: ResourceID used to find address of handler to be used for deposit.

params.depositNonce: ID of deposited generated by origin Bridge contract.
params.destinationChainID: ID of chain where proposal is executed.
params.resourceID: ResourceID to be used when making deposits.

params.chainID: ID of chain the Bridge contract exists on.

ownableInit(address).details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.handlerAddress: Address of handler resource will be set for.
params.tokenAddress: Address of contract to be called when a deposit is made and a deposited is executed.

setNativeResourceID(bytes32).details: can only be called through admin address

params.handlerAddress: Address of handler resource will be set for.
params.resourceID: ResourceID to be used when making deposits.
params.tokenAddress: Address of contract to be called when a deposit is made and a deposited is executed.

sub(uint256,uint256).details: Returns the subtraction of two unsigned integers, reverting on overflow (when the result is negative).     * Counterpart to Solidity's `-` operator.     * Requirements: - Subtraction cannot overflow.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Facilitates deposits, creation and votiing of deposit proposals, and deposit executions.

devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. * By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. * This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

ownableInit(address).details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

@dev Contract module which allows children to implement an emergency stop
mechanism that can be triggered by an authorized account.
 * This is a stripped down version of Open zeppelin's Pausable contract.
https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/EnumerableSet.sol
@dev Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.
@dev Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.
@dev Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

@dev Wrappers over Solidity's arithmetic operations with added overflow
checks.
 * note that this is a stripped down version of open zeppelin's safemath
https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/math/SafeMath.sol

@dev Returns the subtraction of two unsigned integers, reverting on
overflow (when the result is negative).
     * Counterpart to Solidity's `-` operator.
     * Requirements:
- Subtraction cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the subtraction of two unsigned integers, reverting with custom message on
overflow (when the result is negative).
     * Counterpart to Solidity's `-` operator.
     * Requirements:
- Subtraction cannot overflow.

@dev Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where
there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to
specific functions.
 * By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This
can later be changed with {transferOwnership}.
 * This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier
`onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to
the owner.
@dev Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.
@dev Returns the address of the current owner.
@dev Throws if called by any account other than the owner.

@dev Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call
`onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.
     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner,
thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

@dev Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`).
Can only be called by the current owner.
